  "text": "Tinea faciei is a relatively rare dermatophyte infection that occurs on the non-bearded regions of the face. The condition is usually misdiagnosed due to its atypical clinical symptoms. Treatment with corticosteroids makes its presentations incognito. [CITATION_1] The most frequent agents of the infection are Trichophyton mentagrophytes complex, followed by Microsporum canis and Microsporum gypseum. [CITATION_2] T.",
